    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1944-11-22T22:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1944-11-22T22:00:00-05:00" n="544"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d544">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">800.42/11–1844: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        the Ambassador in the United Kingdom</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Winant</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1944-11-22T23:00:00-04:00"
                            >November 22, 1944—11 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>9840. Kefauver to Johnson. Reference Embassy’s 8910, October 18. Special
                    appropriation by Congress would be necessary to provide funds for emergency aid.
                    Problem being studied in Department. Not feasible just now to request such
                    appropriation in view of enabling legislation before Congress. Independent
                    action by British Government would not be embarrassing. Instead Department would
                    be pleased that emergency needs could be met.</p>
                <p>Definite that army will not handle basic scholastic equipment needs except on
                    spot requisition by field commander. Some such requisitions coming through.
                    Ministers of education should indicate importance and urgency of need which
                    cannot be met locally to head of army Civil Affairs Mission for his
                    consideration for spot requisition. [Kefauver.]</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Stettinius</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
